Days over 100
Which years had the most days of 100+ temperature? i.e., group by year and count the number of days with 100+ temps.

weather |&gt;
  filter(tmax &gt;= 100) |&gt;
  group_by(year = year(date)) |&gt;
  summarize(days_100_plus = n()) |&gt;
  arrange(desc(days_100_plus)) |&gt;
  filter(days_100_plus &gt;= 50)

# A tibble: 7 × 2
   year days_100_plus
  &lt;dbl&gt;         &lt;int&gt;
1  2011            90
2  2023            80
3  2009            68
4  2022            68
5  2019            57
6  2018            52
7  2008            50


Data Takeaway: In 2011, Austin experienced 90 days with temperatures over 100 degrees, beating out 2023 by 10 more days over 100 degrees.
